  "text": "The CSI driver integration in kubernetes/kubernetes spans two main areas: (1) The `pkg/volume/csi/` package implements the kubelet-side CSI node plugin client \u2014 `csi_client.go` defines the gRPC client interface (`csiClient`) and implementation (`csiDriverClient`) that wraps CSI Node RPCs (NodeStageVolume, NodePublishVolume, NodeGetInfo, etc.); `csi_plugin.go` implements the volume.VolumePlugin interface (`csiPlugin`); `csi_attacher.go` handles attach/detach via VolumeAttachment objects (`csiAttacher`); `csi_mounter.go` implements mount/unmount (`csiMountMgr`); `csi_block.go` handles raw block volumes (`csiBlockMapper`); `csi_drivers_store.go` tracks registered CSI drivers; `csi_metrics.go` provides metrics via NodeGetVolumeStats; `csi_util.go` has helper utilities; `expander.go` implements NodeExpand; and `nodeinfomanager/nodeinfomanager.go` manages CSINode objects. (2) The controller-side: `pkg/controller/volume/attachdetach/` implements the attach/detach controller that orchestrates VolumeAttachment creation/deletion for CSI volumes; `pkg/controller/volume/persistentvolume/pv_controller.go` and `pv_controller_base.go` implement the PersistentVolume controller that bridges provisioning/deletion/binding with CSI via annotations and CSI migration; `volume_host.go` implements VolumeHost for the PV controller; `index.go` provides PV indexing; and `pkg/controller/volume/expand/expand_controller.go` handles CSI volume expansion. The `pkg/volume/csimigration/plugin_manager.go` provides the migration layer between in-tree and CSI plugins.",
